obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42482)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42482&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Judicial Appointments`
  line `Commission Act, 2014.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 13th April, 2015, vide notification No. S.O. 1001(E), dated by 13th April, 2015, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42483)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42483&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commission" means the National Judicial Appointments Commission referred to in article`
  line `124A of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) "High Court" means the High Court in respect of which recommendation for appointment of a`
  line `Judge is proposed to be made by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(d) "Member" means a Member of the Commission and includes its Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by the rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Commission under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42484)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Headquarters of Commission.`
  content `The Headquarters of the Commission shall be at Delhi.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42484&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42485)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Reference to Commission for filling up of vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42485&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)The Central Government shall, within`
  line `a period of thirty days from the date of coming into force of this Act, intimate the vacancies existing in`
  line `the posts of Judges in the Supreme Court and in a High Court to the Commission for making its`
  line `recommendations to fill up such vacancies.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall, six months prior to the date of occurrence of any vacancy by`
  line `reason of completion of the term of a Judge of the Supreme Court or of a High Court, make a reference to`
  line `the Commission for making its recommendation to fill up such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall, within a period of thirty days from the date of occurrence of any`
  line `vacancy by reason of death or resignation of a Judge of the Supreme Court or of a High Court, make a`
  line `reference to the Commission for making its recommendations to fill up such vacancy.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42486)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Procedure for selection of Judge of Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42486&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall recommend for`
  line `appointment the senior-most Judge of the Supreme Court as the Chief Justice of India if he is considered`
  line `fit to hold the office:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member of the Commission whose name is being considered for recommendation`
  line `shall not participate in the meeting.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, on the basis of ability, merit and any other criteria of suitability as may be`
  line `specified by regulations, recommend the name for appointment as a Judge of the Supreme Court from`
  line `amongst persons who are eligible to be appointed as such under clause (3) of article 124 of the`
  line `Constitution:`
  line
  line `Provided that while making recommendation for appointment of a High Court Judge, apart from`
  line `seniority, the ability and merit of such Judge shall be considered:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Commission shall not recommend a person for appointment if any two`
  line `members of the Commission do not agree for such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission may, by regulations, specify such other procedure and conditions for selection`
  line `and appointment of a Judge of the Supreme Court as it may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42487)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procedure for selection of Judge of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42487&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall recommend for`
  line `appointment a Judge of a High Court to be the Chief Justice of a High Court on the basis of inter se`
  line `seniority of High Court Judges and ability, merit and any other criteria of suitability as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall seek nomination from the Chief Justice of the concerned High Court for`
  line `the purpose of recommending for appointment a person to be a Judge of that.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall also on the basis of ability, merit and any other criteria of suitability as may`
  line `be specified by regulations, nominate name for appointment as a Judge of a High Court from amongst`
  line `persons who are eligible to be appointed as such under clause (2) of article 217 of the Constitution and`
  line `forward such names to the Chief Justice of the concerned High Court for its views.`
  line
  line `(4) Before making any nomination under sub-section (2) or giving its views under sub-section (3), the`
  line `Chief Justice of the concerned High Court shall consult two senior-most Judges of that High Court and`
  line `such other Judges and eminent advocates of that High Court as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) After receiving views and nomination under sub-sections (2) and (3), the Commission may`
  line `recommend for appointment the person who is found suitable on the basis of ability, merit and any other`
  line `criteria of suitability as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commission shall not recommend a person for appointment under this section if any two`
  line `members of the Commission do not agree for such recommendation.`
  line
  line `(7) The Commission shall elicit in writing the views of the Governor and the Chief Minister of the`
  line `State concerned before making such recommendation in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(8) The Commission may, by regulations, specify such other procedure and conditions for selection`
  line `and appointment of a Chief Justice of a High Court and a Judge of a High Court as it may consider`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42488)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of President to require reconsideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42488&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The President shall, on the recommendations`
  line `made by the Commission, appoint the Chief Justice of India or a Judge of the Supreme Court or, as the`
  line `case may be, the Chief Justice of a High Court or the Judge of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President may, if considers necessary, require the Commission to reconsider, either`
  line `generally or otherwise, the recommendation made by it:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Commission makes a recommendation after reconsideration in accordance`
  line `with the provisions contained in sections 5 or 6, the President shall make the appointment accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42489)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Officers and employees of Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42489&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with`
  line `the Commission, appoint such number of officers and other employees for the discharge of functions of`
  line `the Commission under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and other conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Commission`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Conveyor of the Commission shall be the Secretary to the Government of India in the`
  line `Department of Justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42490)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure for transfer of Judges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42490&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall recommend for transfer of Chief`
  line `Justices and other Judges of High Courts from one High Court to any other High Court, and for this`
  line `purpose, specify, by regulations, the procedure for such transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42491)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure to be followed by Commission in discharge of its functions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42491&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission`
  line `shall have the power to specify, by regulations, the procedure for the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall meet at such time and place as the Chairperson may direct and observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at its`
  line `meeting), as it may specify by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42492)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42492&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:––`
  line
  line `(a) the fees and allowances payable to the eminent persons nominated under sub-clause (d) of`
  line `clause (1) of article 124A of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and other conditions of service of officers and other employees of the Commission`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed, in respect of which provision is to be`
  line `made by the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42493)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42493&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make regulations consistent with this Act, and the rules made thereunder, to carry out the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the criteria of suitability with respect to appointment of a Judge of the Supreme Court under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) other procedure and conditions for selection and appointment of a Judge of the Supreme Court`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the criteria of suitability with respect to appointment of a Judge of the High Court under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) other Judges and eminent advocates who may be consulted by the Chief Justice under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of eliciting views of the Governor and the Chief Minister under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) other procedure and conditions for selection and appointment of a Judge of the High Court`
  line `under sub-section (8) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure for transfer of Chief Justices and other Judges from one High Court to any other`
  line `High Court under section 9;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure to be followed by the Commission in the discharge of its functions under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(i) the rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at the meetings of Commission,`
  line `including the quorum at its meeting, under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (42494)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42494&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and regulation made under this`
  line `Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in`
  line `session, for a total period of thirty days, which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (42495)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088&sectionId=42495&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_3_00021_201440_1517807328088
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, after consultation with the Commission, by an order published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it`
  line `to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of five years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
